IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Seed Specification Langauge or Seed Spec in this repo is a language under development and your task is to incrementally improve the language and it's libraries and tooling given the purpose and objective of the language in Readme.md file.
- Readme file always provides the best top level ground truth for this project. If there are conflicts or inconsistencies between the readme and other files, ask the user about the choices and fix the inconsistencies.
- Always try to keep things to a minimum. Keep all changes as incremental as possible. Don't make too many changes at once.
- The "concepts and structure" file contains the basic concepts and grammar of the SeedSpec language in BNF form.
- Always update the "concepts and structure" file whenever changes are made to any documentation to keep it consistent with the current state of the language.
